{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Nm7bQLKDhH7eHPF5a2BdC2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01R5CuLtwV1AyHmKp7e1U2bn","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Cron parser rejects invalid expressions with a descriptive error message","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure lives entirely inside the parser's validation logic — bad input in, error out. No module boundaries involved. REAL-INFRA: No OS, network, or subprocess. MOCK-HIDE: Nothing to mock; the function under test is a pure string-to-structure transformer. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but rejected — there is no handoff to another module where a failure could hide; the parser itself either accepts or rejects the expression.","test_description":"Call the cron parser directly with a table of invalid inputs (month=13, day=32, hour=25, malformed field counts, empty strings, non-numeric fields) and assert each raises the expected error type with a message that names the offending component. Also verify that a valid expression does NOT raise, to confirm the error path is specific.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Next-run-time calculator returns correct timestamps for standard and edge-case cron expressions","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: This is a deterministic computation — cron expression + start time → list of timestamps. The failure mode is wrong arithmetic or wrong calendar logic (e.g., off-by-one on 'last day of month'), which is entirely within the calculator module. REAL-INFRA: Date math is in-process; no OS or network needed. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the calendar library would hide the real failure, so use real date objects — but that is still in-process. REJECTION-GATE: Integration rejected